.\" Man page for _printf — Holberton School
.TH _PRINTF 3 "2025" "Holberton School" "Custom C Library"

.SH NAME
_printf \- custom implementation of printf

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.PP
.BI "int _printf(const char *" "format" ", ...);"

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf()
function produces output according to a
.I format
string and writes it to stdout.
.PP
The format string may contain conversion specifiers,
each introduced by the character
.BR % .

.SS Conversion specifiers
.TP
.B c
Prints a single character.
.TP
.B s
Prints a null-terminated string.
.TP
.B d, i
Prints a signed decimal integer.
.TP
.B %%
Prints a literal percent sign.

.SH RETURN VALUE
On success,
.B _printf()
returns the number of characters printed,
excluding the terminating null byte.
On error, it returns \-1.

.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
#include "main.h"

_printf("Hello, %s!\n", "world");
_printf("Number: %d\n", 42);

.fi

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf (3),
.BR write (2),
.BR va_start (3)

